Reaching some kind of low point right now. A combination of being flattened by heartbreak, the suffocating anxiety leading up to it, and isolating after catching covid - all within the same couple of weeks. I am cuckoo crazy in the bad way. 

Though it has been nice(?) having time to reflect on my pattern of pursuing people who want little to do with me. Finding myself hoping, praying, willing to forgive, expecting less, accepting neglect, all in the belief that it’ll work out in the end. I want to escape this loop. And I guess awareness is the first step. Though it’s hard to imagine changing when I am so easily conquered by hope, when I am someone who inherently (foolishly?) believes in love and all of its possibilities.

Btw, how do I make a post close friends only?? Asking for a friend..
